<item>
            <title>[HIVE-4320] Consider extending max limit for precision to 38</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-4320</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Max precision of 38 still fits in 128. It changes the way you do math on these numbers though. Need to see if there will be perf implications, but there&apos;s a strong case to support 38 (instead of 36) to comply with other DBs. (Oracle, SQL Server, Teradata).&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
