                            <comment id="13628542" author="hagleitn" created="Thu, 11 Apr 2013 01:30:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thought about this some more and did some testing. Comparing storing two&apos;s complement in two longs v packing 9 digits shouldn&apos;t have a performance impact. The latter method does seem make implementation easier (add/sub will not overflow, multiplication won&apos;t overflow in long). So, all in all it&apos;s better to be aligned with other DBs than gain a little more leeway in implementing these operations.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13630754" author="hagleitn" created="Fri, 12 Apr 2013 23:29:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Review: &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.facebook.net/D10227&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reviews.facebook.net/D10227&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13631957" author="ashutoshc" created="Mon, 15 Apr 2013 18:10:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 will commit if tests pass.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13632202" author="hagleitn" created="Mon, 15 Apr 2013 21:15:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It would be good to have this in 0.11 as well, so we don&apos;t have different max limit between versions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13632518" author="ashutoshc" created="Tue, 16 Apr 2013 02:54:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Test &lt;tt&gt;decimal_udf.q&lt;/tt&gt; failed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13632578" author="hagleitn" created="Tue, 16 Apr 2013 05:15:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My apologies. I forgot to include the updates to the golden file for decimal_udf.q in the patch. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-4320&quot; title=&quot;Consider extending max limit for precision to 38&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-4320&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-4320&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.2.patch has it (if you diff the two patches you&apos;ll see that it&apos;s the only change).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13632882" author="ashutoshc" created="Tue, 16 Apr 2013 14:39:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Test &lt;tt&gt;decimal_precision.q&lt;/tt&gt; is now failing, after commit of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-4327&quot; title=&quot;NPE in constant folding with decimal&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-4327&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-4327&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13633289" author="ashutoshc" created="Tue, 16 Apr 2013 20:14:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My bad. Test passed when I ran it again. I must be doing something wrong earlier.&lt;br/&gt;
Committed to trunk and 0.11. Thanks, Gunther!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
